{"id":1261,"date":"2017-01-03T13:22:45","date_gmt":"2017-01-03T18:22:45","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/?p=1261"},"modified":"2017-05-23T12:36:46","modified_gmt":"2017-05-23T16:36:46","slug":"meet-nikki-rothwell-icp-researcher-and-cidermaker","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/meet-nikki-rothwell-icp-researcher-and-cidermaker\/","title":{"rendered":"Meet Nikki Rothwell, ICP Researcher and Cidermaker"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"fcbkbttn_buttons_block\" id=\"fcbkbttn_left\"><\/div><div id=\"attachment_1263\" style=\"width: 710px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/KarenPowers_ICP_MI_Cherry-1-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1263\" class=\"wp-image-1263 size-large\" src=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/KarenPowers_ICP_MI_Cherry-1-1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"Nikki Rothwell (at right) with Project ICP Michigan cherry researchers and field assistants in spring 2015. Photo: Karen Powers.\" width=\"700\" height=\"525\" srcset=\"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/KarenPowers_ICP_MI_Cherry-1-1-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/KarenPowers_ICP_MI_Cherry-1-1-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/01\/KarenPowers_ICP_MI_Cherry-1-1-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-1263\" class=\"wp-caption-text\"><em>Nikki Rothwell (at right) with Project ICP Michigan cherry researchers and field assistants in spring 2015. Photo: Karen Powers.<\/em><\/p><\/div>\n<p>Michigan State University AgBioResearch <a href=\"http:\/\/agbioresearch.msu.edu\/news\/researcher_qa_nikki_rothwell\">recently profiled Dr. Nikki Rothwell<\/a>, coordinator of the Northwest Michigan Horticultural Research Center, Project ICP researcher working on cherry pollination, and award-winning cidermaker.<\/p>\n<p>Dr. Rothwell has been\u00a0at the MSU research center\u00a0since 2004, and works closely with the local grower community to develop new areas of research and communicate research results. \u201cI\u2019m lucky that I got to come home to Michigan, and I get to work at a place like <abbr title=\"Michigan State University\">MSU<\/abbr> that\u2019s so supportive,\u201d Rothwell said. \u201cWe have a strong backing from growers who are really invested in our research. We are in a position to assist them because of MSU\u2019s commitment and the industry\u2019s support, and as an extension professional, you can\u2019t ask for more.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>In 2008, she opened <a href=\"http:\/\/www.tandemciders.com\/\">Tandem Ciders<\/a> with husband Dan Young. The cider business is growing steadily, and the tasting room &#8211; close to the research center &#8211; is open year-round. Learn more in Rothwell&#8217;s AgBioResearch feature story and Q&amp;A here:\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/agbioresearch.msu.edu\/news\/researcher_qa_nikki_rothwell\">http:\/\/agbioresearch.msu.edu\/news\/researcher_qa_nikki_rothwell<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Michigan State University AgBioResearch recently profiled Dr. Nikki Rothwell, coordinator of the Northwest Michigan Horticultural Research Center, Project ICP researcher working on cherry pollination, and award-winning cidermaker. Dr. Rothwell has been\u00a0at the MSU research center\u00a0since 2004, and works closely with&hellip; <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":5,"featured_media":1263,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_exactmetrics_skip_tracking":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_active":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_note":"","_exactmetrics_sitenote_category":0,"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":true,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_conta